<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2008-01-15</DATELINE><TITLE>Thiol-based angiotensin-converting enzyme 2 inhibitors: P1 modifications for the exploration of the S1 subsite</TITLE><BODY>Abstract Screening of a metalloprotease library led to the identification of a thiol-based dual ACE/NEP inhibitor as a potent ACE2 inhibitor. Modifications of the P1 benzyl moiety led to improvements in ACE2 potency as well as to increased selectivity versus ACE and NEP.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>